    "patch_code": "public static int[] parseVersionTriplet(String verStr) {\n        final List<Integer> triplet = new ArrayList<Integer>();\n        int count = 0;\n        try {\n            for (final String segment : verStr.split(\"\\\\.\")) {\n                if (!segment.isEmpty()) {\n                    triplet.add(Integer.parseInt(segment));\n                    ++count;\n                } else if (count == 0){\n                    triplet.add(0);\n                    ++count;\n                } else {\n                    while (count < 3) {\n                        triplet.add(0);\n                        ++count;\n                    }\n                }\n            }\n        } catch (NumberFormatException ex) {\n            throw new IllegalArgumentException(verStr + \" is not a valid version string\");\n        }\n        \n        // Return an array with size of max 3\n        int[] retVal=new int[3];\n        for (int i = 0;i < triplet.size() ;i ++){\n             retVal[i]=triplet.get(i).intValue();\n        }\n        \n        return retVal;\n    }",
